					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can't use ROM offsets for Game Genie codes. You have to find out where this code is mapped in the addressing space of the NES (probably somewhere between $8000 and $FFFF).
<br />
<br />Since you have a search string, you can open the game in FCEUXD, open its Hex Editor (under the "Tools" menu) and search for the string there. Once you find the string you can see where the byte you want to change is.</div>

