				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Game Genie codes have nothing to do with the Rom File address, and all to do with the address of the bank within the NES's memory.
<br />
<br />For instance, Zelda uses 16K bankswitching, with the last bank as the fixed bank.  Any bank besides the last one would be mapped in at 8000.  So something at 0x6565 in the file would be located at 0xA555 in memory.</div>

					
