						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">ROM C000-FFFF is fixed to the last PRG bank.  (last 16k)<br />ROM 8000-BFFF is the switchable bank.</div>
<br />That's true of games that use SNROM as if it were UNROM, like Zelda. But other games might use it like BNROM (swap 32 KiB at a time) or more rarely like Crazy Climber ($8000 fixed to first 16 KiB bank, $C000 switchable). I seem to remember a Zelda-based pirate multi using 32 KiB bank mode for the NROM games it contained.</div>

